Flatter and on the stumps, Ravindra keeps it out.
On middle, defended.
Floats it up on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Tim Southee walks out to bat.

OUT! LBW! There goes another one. India just the two wickets away. The second new ball does the trick! This is flatter and on middle, it lands and then turns away. Kyle Jamieson lunges forward to defend but does so inside the line. It goes past the outside edge and hits the back pad. A huge appeal and the finger is raised. Kyle Jamieson knew he has out and he just started to walk back.
Shortish and on off, it is pushed to covers.
This one is angled into the pads, Kyle Jamieson looks to flick but misses.
Fires it on middle, Kyle Jamieson keeps it out.
Half an appeal but turned down! Fires it on the pads, Kyle Jamieson looks to defend, there are two noises but it seems like it is bat on pad.
Flatter and on off, defended.

Dropped! Loopy ball, on the pads. Kyle Jamieson looks to work it away but gets the inside edge on the pads. Pujara is late to react at short leg and the ball goes past him. A very, very tough chance to be honest.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Shorter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Carrom ball! It lands on off and goes away. Kyle Jamieson is stuck to his crease while looking to block. The ball goes past the outside edge.
Shorter ball, on off. It keeps low but Kyle Jamieson gets his bat on it.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Blocked out.
FINALLY! The second new ball has been taken!
Fuller and on off. Rachin Ravindra goes back and blocks it.
Full and on off. Kyle Jamieson pushes it past point for one.
Shorter ball, around off. Pushed past covers for a couple.
Flatter ball, on off. It stays very low but Kyle Jamieson goes back and blocks.
Past short leg! Kyle Jamieson gets forward to defend but gest the inside edge past short leg.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.

DRINKS! This is turning out to be a nail-biting finish here! Just the three wickets needed and there are over 10 overs to go. The second new ball is available but not taken yet. The pitch has started to play tricks a lot more than we have seen in this game. The Indian bowlers are bowling well but Rachin Ravindra and Kyle Jamieson are up to the task so far. India though know another wicket here and they can surely get the remaining two quickly. For New Zealand, a lot depends on this pair. An exciting one hour or so remains.
Beaten! Fuller ball, just outside off. Ravindra looks to block but the ball stays low and goes past the bat. Another over goes by.
Nicely tossed up, outside off. Ravindra gets forward and then leaves it.
Loopy ball, on leg. Ravindra gets forward to block it.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Worked down to long on for one.
Shorter ball, on off. Kyle Jamieson goes back and blocks it.
Fuller ball, on middle. Kyle Jamieson gets the inside edge but to the right of short leg.
Shorter ball, outside off. It comes in but not enough and is left alone.
FOUR! Past first slip! Tossed up, outside off. Ravindra gets forward to defend but gets the outside edge. The man at first slip dives but cannot get to the ball. It races to the fence.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Shorter ball, lands outside off and comes back in. Rachin Ravindra goes back and blocks it.
Loopy ball, around off. A solid front foot defence by Ravindra.
Fuller ball, outside off. Ravindra gets forward to block it.
Kyle Jamieson goes back and blocks this one. One more over negotiated.
Tossed up, on the pads. Kyle Jamieson blocks it out.
Shorter ball, outside off. Kyle Jamieson taps it to cover.
Full ball, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Shorter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, outside off. Kyle Jamieson leaves it alone.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
On middle, defended.
Vicious turn now! This lands outside off and spins back in a lot. Rachin Ravindra looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. HIgh on the pads we should say.
Fires it on middle, defended.
Rachin Ravindra has reviewed this LBW decision. No bat on that. But the impact is outside off.

NOT OUT! THE IMPACT IS OUTSIDE OFF! The New Zealand will camp will breathe a huge sigh of releif. Ravindra survives. He is the last recognized batter. However, this is not a wicket which you should be playing back but the good thing is, he got his pads outside the line of off. This is flatter and outside off, spins back in sharply and also stays low. Ravnidra stays back and looks to defend but it sneaks under the bat and hits the pad. An appeal and the finger is raised. Rachin Ravindra reviews and replays show that the on-field call has to be overturned.
On off, Rachin keeps it out.
A dot to end! A wicket-maiden! On off, Kyle is solid in defense.
Loopy ball on off, Kyle Jamieson stays back and pushes it to mid off.
Another one tossed up on off, defended.
Floats it up on middle, blocked.
Kyle Jamieson is the next batter.

OUT! TIMBER! That is one of the strangest dismissals seen! Blundell can consider himself a tad unlucky. India won't care though as they are now in the bowling all-rounders. Just the three wickets away now with over 15 overs left. This is an off spinner. It lands on off and turns back in. Blundell looks to defend, it hits the inner half, lands beside him but on a footmark, it spins back onto the stumps and clips the leg bail. He can't believe what has just happened. Shakes his head as he walks back. Just like the first innings, he was looking solid but falls in an unfortunate manner.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
A maiden from Jadeja! On middle, defended.
On middle, Rachin Ravindra negotiates it.
Again, darts it on the stumps, Ravindra gets his bat down in time.
Fires it on middle, kept out.
Flatter and quicker outside off, this one goes on with the arm. Rachindra looks to defend but does so inside the line, he is beaten.
On off, turns back in a little. Blocked.
Review time! India have taken the review for LBW. No bat on that but it is going down the leg stumps!

NOT OUT! It is spinning down leg! We felt that would be the case! This lands outside off and then turns back in. Blundell looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. A huge appeal but turned down. After a long chat, Rahane reviews. Replays show that India lose a review.
Three more! Angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wiket for three.
Slightly fuller and on middle, Racin prods forward and keeps it out.
Angled into the pads, RR works it to square leg.
Gives it air and on middle, defended.
Flatter and on middle, Rachin stands back and blocks.
A round-arm action this time, it is delivered on middle, defended.
Relentless stuff! Continues to attack the middle pole, Blundell is solid in defense.
Another one on the stumps, Blundell manages to block it.
On off, Blundell pushes it to covers.
Yet again on the stumps, blocked.
Darts it on middle, defended.
Floats it up on off, Ravindra plays it to mid on.
Quicker and fuller on middle, blocked.
Another one on middle, Ravindra leans forward and keeps it out.
On the stumps, Rachin keeps it out with ease.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Gives it a little air and lands it on off, defended.
On off, Blundell gets right behind the line and defends.
Angled in on middle, Tom negotiates it with ease.
On the stumps, kept out.
Another one on middle, Blundell keeps it out.
Flatter and on middle, Tom hangs back and lets it be.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR BYES! That has taken off! It lands in the rough outside off, pitches and then spins and bounces back in sharply. Ravindra leaves it. The keeper does not get his gloves high up in time and it goes to the fine leg fence.
Shorter and on off, Ravindra pushes it to covers.
Patel has two short legs in place for Rachin Ravindra.
Gives it air and lands it on middle, it is played back to the bowler.
Floats it up on off, Ravindra defends.
On the stumps, yet another defensive stroke. The keeper in hindi says all they are doing is blocking and rightly so.
Floats it up on off, Rachin blocks.
Solid again! On middle, Blundell leans forward and keeps it out.
On middle, Blundell blocks.
Good turn there! This lands around leg and then holds its line. Blundell looks to work it on the leg side but it goes off the leading edge, a soft one to gully.
On off, Blundell prods forward and keeps it out.
Slip, a kneeling gully and a silly point in place.
Angled into the pads, Blundell works it to square leg.
Flatter and on off, Blundell lunges and defends it solidly.
From around the wicket now, this is bowled on middle, Ravindra is solid in defense.
Another one tossed up nicely, it lands on off, Ravindra pushes it to covers.
Loopy delivery and on off, Rachin opens the face of the bat and guides it to point.
Tosses it up on off, Ravindra defends it.
Slightly shorter and on off, it is pushed to covers.
Flatter and on off, RR goes back and blocks.
Tossed up, outside off. Ravindra gets the outside edge while looking to block. The ball runs past first slip and the batters take three before the fielder cuts it off.
Shorter ball, outside off. Left alone.
Flatter ball, outside off. It goes straight with the angle. Ravindra gets across to block but gets beaten.
Shorter again, outside off. Ravindra goes back and blocks it.
Shorter ball, around off. Blocked out.
Rachin Ravindra walks out to bat! It is Jadeja who got him in the first innings and he will be facing him here first up.

OUT! LBW! SUPERSTAR JADEJA DOES IT! He gets the biggest wicket for India! Shorter ball, around off. It comes in with the angle. No spin whatsoever. The trick here is that it stays very, very low. Kane Williamson decides to go back and that proves his undoing. The ball hits him on the pads and Ravindra Jadeja brings out the celebrappeal! The umpire has no doubt and raises the finger.
A solid defence off the front foot to end the over.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Beaten again! Angled, just outside off. Blundell gets forward but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Kept low! Tossed up, outside off. Blundell goes forward to block but the ball turns away and keeps low to beat the outside edge.
Full and on off. Blundell puts in a good stride and blocks it.
Loopy ball, around off. Blundell drives it to covers.
Flatter ball, around off. Tapped to point.
Fuller ball, on off. Kane Williamson pushes it straight to the newly-place silly point.
Silly point is in place now.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Back to defending it nicely is Kane Williamson.
Beauty! Jadeja bowls this a bit shorter, on off. Williamson doesn't get the biggest stride as he looks to block. The ball turns sharply and goes past the outside edge.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Flatter ball, on off. It stays low as Blundell goes back. But he gets low enough to block it.
Fuller and on the pads. Blundell gets forward and taps it to short leg.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Flatter ball, on off. Tom blocks it right under his eyes.
Tom Blundell puts in a nice stride and blocks it well.
Fuller and on the pads. Tapped to short leg.
Shorter ball, around off. Kane goes back and works it to the off side.
Fuller and a bit slower, on off. Kane Williamson blocks it.
Shorter ball, outside off. Pushed to point.
Angled on off. Kane taps it back to Jadeja.
Shorter ball, around off. Kane Williamson stays in the crease and blocks it.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Tom Blundell works it past square leg for a couple.
Short again, outside off. Pushed to mid on.
Shorter ball, on off. Blundell blocks it from the crease.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Review time! Henry Nicholls has reviewed this but he looks out. No bat on that. OUT IT IS!

OUT! LBW! DEAD STRAIGHT! Patel starts the session with a big wicket! Tossed up, on off. The ball goes pretty much straight after landing. Nicholls plays for a bit of turn and blocks down the wrong line. The ball goes onto hit his pads right in front of the stumps and the finger goes up! The review is taken in hope but there is no bat on that the ball is crashing on the stumps. Tom Blundell walks out to bat.
Axar Patel to continue from the other end.
Quicker and outside off. Kane Williamson watches as Srikar Bharat collects this.
Tossed up, outside off. Kane Williamson gets forward and blocks it.
Shorter ball, on middle and leg. Worked to square leg for a single. Nicholls is off the mark.
Shorter ball, outside off. Henry Nicholls goes back and blocks it.
Fuller ball, on middle and leg. Nicholls blocks this with ease.
We are back for the final session! Henry Nicholls will join Kane Williamson in the middle. Ravindra Jadeja will finish his over. Here comes the last session...
... DAY 5, SESSION 3 ...

Three wickets is what New Zealand have lost in this session and they will be pretty disappointed. Somerville fell on the very first ball after the Lunch break. Latham and Williamson then fought hard but Ashwin got rid of the left-hander. Williamson and Taylor then began the blockathon and it seemed like the Kiwis would head into Tea three down but then Jadeja struck gold. A lot will depend on Williamson now, he needs to hang in there, probably till the end. Can the others handle the pressure? An exciting last session awaits so do join us at 2:30 pm Local (9 am GMT) for the same!

A wicket right at the stroke of Tea has changed things! A draw looked the most likely result when Williamson and Taylor were there but that has now changed, India are into the middle order of the Kiwis which can be termed as fragile and they have just over 30 overs. The hosts would surely fancy their chances especially with the new ball around the corner. The key is, they need to be patient and just hit the right lines and lengths.

OUT! LBW! Ravindra Jadeja strikes just at the stroke of Tea and it is Ross Taylor who walks back to the hut! He never looked comfortable out in the middle and his struggle against left-arm spinners continues. Jadeja bowls it quicker through the air and lands it around off, the ball goes on with the angle. Taylor gets forward to block but he misses and gets trapped in front. Jadeja puts in an appeal and the umpire raises his finger in no time! Huge wicket this for India as New Zealand lose their fourth wicket. That will be Tea on Day 5!
Floated, around leg. Kane Williamson looks to sweep but gets the toe end towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up, around leg. Kane Williamson gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it out.
Tossed up, down leg. Kane Williamson prods but does not offer any shot.
Patel spills this one down leg. Kane Williamson misses his sweep.
Floated, on a length, around leg. Williamson blocks it with ease.
Tossed up, around middle. Kane Williamson defends it out.
Ross Taylor is off the mark! Darted on the pads, Taylor clips it behind square on the leg side and collects a couple.
Tossed up, on a length, around middle. Ross Taylor tucks it to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, outside off. Taylor drives it straight back to the bowler.
Fuller in length, outside off. Ross Taylor drives it to mid off.
An appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved! Flatter ball, coming in with the angle from middle. Ross Taylor looks to defend but misses and gets hit on his pad. Probably it was going down leg.
Tossed up, around off. Ross Taylor presses forward to defend.
Tossed up, outside off. Kane Williamson defends it off the front foot.
Just a tad short, outside off. Kane Williamson punches it to cover. Ross Taylor wanted a single but was rightly sent back by Williamson.
Tossed up, on a length, around off. Kane Williamson keeps it out.
Flatter ball, around off. Kane Williamson dabs it into the deck.
Slower through the air, on a length, outside off. Kane Williamson rocks back and defends this one.
Tossed up, outside off. Kane Williamson blocks this one out.
Fuller in length, outside off. Ross Taylor prods and drives it to cover-point.
NO BALL! BEATEN! Nicely tossed up, outside off, turning away late. Taylor looks to defend but the ball spins past his outside edge.
Flatter ball, outside off. Ross Taylor punches it to cover.
On a length, outside off. Ross Taylor blocks this one out.
Loopy ball, fuller in length, around leg. Ross Taylor nudges it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, darted on the pads. Taylor turns it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, around off. Ross Taylor defends it out.
Another maiden from Ashwin! A carrom ball, on a length, outside off. Kane Williamson comes forward to defend this one.
A half-tracker from Ashwin, around middle. Kane Williamson pulls but straight to the square leg fielder.
Tossed up, fuller in length, outside off. Kane Williamson pushes it to cover.
Loopy ball, around off. Kane Williamson presses forward to block.
Flatter ball, on middle. Kane Williamson turns it to square leg.
Tossed up, on a length, around off. Kane Williamson defends it out.
Darted on the pads. Taylor works it to the leg side.
Loopy ball, outside off. Kane Williamson pushes it to deep cover for one.
Fuller ball, on off. Kane gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Shorter ball, outside off. Kane Williamson gets the inside edge back on the pads while looking to block.
Darted on off. Kane Williamson stays in the crease and blocks it.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.

NOT OUT! Ross Taylor survives! Ashwin errs in line and sprays this one down leg. Taylor looks to flick but misses as the ball spins down leg. Srikar Bharat behind the sticks moves quickly to his left to grab the ball. He whips the bails off and Bharat puts in an appeal! The replays suggests that it was very close than it looked like in real-time but the TV umpire decides to go in the batter's favour as he thinks that Taylor had his back foot grounded and as a result, Taylor escapes!

The TV umpire has been called in. They are checking for stumping of Kane Williamson. No bat on that as they first check UltraEdge. Kane Williamson drags his back foot in but the issue is whether his foot is in the air. But the umpire decides that it is not out.
Tossed up, outside off. Ross Taylor hangs back and blocks it out.
Loopy ball, fuller in length, around leg. Kane Williamson tucks it to wide of mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Nicely tossed up, outside off. Kane Williamson presses forward and dabs it into the deck.
Tossed up, on a length, around middle. Kane Williamson turns it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, around off. Kane Williamson blocks it off the back foot.
Fuller ball, on off. Taylor pushes it to mid off.
Shorter ball, around off. Pushed to covers. No ball called as Jadeja oversteps.
Loopy ball, on off. Taylor comes forward and blocks it.
Shorter ball, outside off. Pushed to deep point for one.
Tossed up, on off. Kane Williamson comes forward and blocks it.
Shorter ball, outside off. Kane taps it towards point.
Loopy ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Shorter ball, outside off. Taylor pushes it to point.
Slips one down the leg side. Left alone.
Sharp turn! Lands outside off and comes back in sharply. Taylor gets hit on the pads and the ball lands short of first slip.
Loopy ball, around off. Blocked out.

OUT! BOWLED! CHOPPED ON! Shorter ball, outside off. Latham looks to push it with his feet glued to the crease. All he gets is the inside edge and the ball goes back onto the stumps! Is that the opening that gets India back in the game? We will see. We surely have an interesting phase of cricket coming up in the next couple of hours. Also, with that wicket, Ravichandran Ashwin has gone past Harbhajan Singh's tally of 417 wickets for India in Tests. Ross Taylor is the next batter.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out by Latham.
Full ball, on off. Kane Williamson puts in a nice stride to block it well.
Darted on the pads. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. Kane Williamson gets forward and blocks it.
Flatter ball, around off. Tapped to first slip.
FOUR! Trademark shot of Kane Williamson! Shorter ball, outside off. He waits for it and then runs it past short third man for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Change. Ravindra Jadeja (6-0-11-0) is back on.
A single as this is pushed down to long on.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Blocked out.
Shorter ball, outside off. Pushed past covers. The man at cover chases it and keeps it to two.
Tossed up, going straight after landing on middle. Kane Williamson blocks it without any issues.
Full ball, on off. Blocked from the front foot.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Williamson works it to square leg.
Length ball, lands outside off and comes back in. Latham shoulders his arms to this.
Full ball, wide outside off. Latham won't chase this one.
Short of a length, outside off. Left alone.
Short of a length, outside off. Latham works it towards mid on.
On a length, outside off. Latham gets forward and blocks it.
Length ball, around off. Blocked out.

FIFTY FOR LATHAM! Darted on the pads. Latham works it past mid-wicket. The fielder chases it and the batters take three. What a knock by Latham though. He scored a fifty in the first innings too and has delivered yet again. The job is still not done.
Shorter ball, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Nicely tossed up, outside off. Latham blocks it off the front foot.
Dot ball as this is pushed to covers.
Tossed up, on off. Latham blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Tapped out.

Drinks! A really good show by New Zealand. Kane Williamson has joined Latham and both of them are looking quite good. It is quite clear that they are playing for a draw here so the Indian bowlers will have to work very hard for their wickets here. There is still plenty of time for them to take the remaining 8 wickets.
Length ball, jagging back in from off. Williamson looks to defend but gets a bit squared up in doing so. The ball goes off the outer half of his blade towards cover.
Ishant bowls it from wider of the crease and bangs it into the deck, around middle. Williamson ducks underneath.
Good-length ball, angling in a bit from middle. Williamson gets behind the line of the ball to block this one.
Back of a length, around off. Williamson stays back and opens the face of his bat to guide it towards backward point.
NO BALL! Ishant Sharma oversteps yet again! Length ball, around off. Williamson defends it solidly off the front foot.
Fuller in length, outside off, inviting the batter to drive. Kane Williamson shoulders arms to this one.
Good-length ball, around off. Kane Williamson stays back to defend it from the crease.
A maiden from Ashwin! Nicely tossed up, around off. Tom Latham blocks this one solidly off the front foot.
On a length, around middle. Tom Latham blocks it watchfully off the back foot.
JAFFA! Drift, grip and turn! Tossed up, around off, turning away late. Tom Latham prods to defend but the ball spins past his blade.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Loopy ball, on off. Latham prods to defend it.
Flatter ball, around off. Tom Latham stays back to block this one out.
Length ball, around the fourth stump. Williamson defends it off the front foot.
Good running! Length ball, on the pads. Williamson flicks it to wide of deep mid-wicket and comes back for the second run.
FOUR! GLORIOUS! Fuller in length, outside off. Williamson presses forward and carves it past Ravindra Jadeja at mid off to collect a boundary.
Good-length ball, outside off. Kane Williamson defends this one out.
Length ball, sprayed down leg. Williamson misses his flick and Srikar Bharat behind the sticks moves across to his left to gather the ball.
Ishant Sharma (4-0-13-0) is back on.
Good-length ball, around middle. Kane Williamson defends it solidly off the back foot.

Just short of the slip fielder! Ashwin tosses it up, outside off. Williamson presses forward to block yet again but it goes off the thick outside edge towards Ajinkya Rahane at first slip, on the bounce. Rahane fails to stop it cleanly and the ball goes past him. The batters take a run.
Loopy ball, on a length, outside off. KW blocks it off the front foot.
Nicely tossed up, outside off. Williamson defends it out.
Finds the gap this time! Flatter ball, darted on the pads. Latham flicks it past square leg and takes a run. New Zealand bring up their 100!
Flatter ball, around middle and leg. Latham tucks it to square leg.
Tossed up, on a length, on off. Latham blocks it off the front foot.
Another maiden over from Yadav! Fuller in length, around the fifth stump. Williamson defends it towards cover.
Good-length ball, around the fourth-stump channel. Williamson presses forward to block this one out.
Another ball, on a length, jagging back in from middle. Williamson turns it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, just outside off. Williamson leaves it alone.
Length ball, angling in slightly from middle. Williamson stays back and looks to block but the ball stays a touch low and hits the bottom of his bat.
Good-length delivery, around off. Kane Williamson gets behind the line of the ball and blocks it back to the bowler.

Unplayable! Can't do a lot there again. There are such deliveries which just manage to turn here and there and that was one of them. Just need to forget it and move ahead. It lands on off and spins away sharply. Latham looks to defend but is beaten.
On middle, Latham works it to mid-wicket.
On middle, Latham defends it with the full face of the bat.
Loopy ball on off, Latham pushes it to covers.
Floats it up on off, Latham leans forward and keeps it out.
Ravichandran Ashwin (12-2-19-1) is back on.
Flatter and on off, Latham stays back and blocks.
A maiden! On off, blocked.
Just as I write that, he drifts one down the leg side. Almost gets a wicket. Williamson looks to flick but misses. The keeper dives to his left and takes it nicely.
On off, really good lines and lengths from Yadav. KW though is solid in defense.
This one stays low! On off, Williamson looks to hang back and defend, it hits the bottom of the bat.
On the stumps, Williamson defends it with ease again.
Another one on the stumps, Williamson plays it back to the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, this is jammed back to the bowler.
On middle, kept out.
Goes back to attacking the stumps, it is played back to the bowler.
Really nicely played! He initially wanted to sweep but then sees, it is short and outside off, he guides it past point for two.
This time he plays a defensive stroke. On middle, blocked.
Outside off, Latham looks to play the reverse sweep but misses. Latham has started to play a few shots now. Not sure if he is worried about the rough or has his approach changed.
On the pads, Williamson flicks but the man at square leg stops it.
On middle, Williamson gets right behind the line and defends.
Angled into the pads, Latham works it through square leg for one.
Angled into the pads, it is worked down to fine leg for one.
On middle, Williamson manages to keep it out again.
Attacks the stumps again, makes the batter play, blocked.
Shorter and into the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! That is a lovely shot! Williamson skips down the track, he gets to the pitch of it and lofts it over the bowler for a boundary.
This time he connects with the sweep, it goes through square leg for one.
Outside off, Latham gets outside the line of off and then tries to sweep but misses to get hit on the pads.

BEATEN! Quite a strange way to defend there. Probably worried about the rough. This lands well outside off, Latham tries to defend it as he is shuffling across. This one goes on with the arm and just about misses the outside edge.
Outside off, shortish. Latham pushes it through covers for two.
Another dot to end! On off, Williamson plays it onto the ground. He is on 1 run of 19 balls.
Another one on a length and around off, Williamson plays it nice and late and on the off side.
Length and on middle, Williamson stays back and defends.
Angled into middle, defended.
How do you play those? Jaffa! This angles into the off pole, pitches and moves away. Williamson is all squared up as he tries to block. It goes past the outside edge and the off pole.
Outside off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Floats it up on off, Williamson strokes it to mid off.
Angled into the middle pole, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, Axar continues to attack the stumps, Williamson plays it to covers.
And again! On middle, Williamson, with soft hands, blocks.
On middle, Williamson lunges forward and keeps it out nicely.
On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Really nicely played! Fuller and on middle, Latham just pushes it past mid on for one.
Another one on a length and around off, Latham lunges forward and blocks.
Another one on a length and around off, Latham defends it solidly.
Outside off and on a length. Left alone.
On middle, fuller again, Latham pushes it to mid on.
FOUR! Through the gap! Probably was all along the ground! Full and outside off, Latham leans and looks to drive, it goes off the outside edge between gully and widish first slip and into the fence.
Angles it into the stumps, Williamson shows the full face of the bat and plays it back to the bowler.
On middle, KW plays yet another defensive stroke.
Attacks the stumps yet again, Williamson comes forward and plays it back to the bowler.
Floats it up on off, Williamson leans forward and keeps it out.
Flatter yet again and on middle, this one stays a touch low. Williamson blocks it onto the ground.
Angled into the pads, Williamson blocks it out.
Axar Patel will start from the other end.
A good over by Umesh Yadav to begin with! Outside off, Latham shoulders arms to this one.
On off, kept out.
Length and on off, this one holds its line. Williamson looks to defend, it goes off the outer half to point for one.
Again on middle, Williamson works it to mid-wicket.
Right on the money to welcome Williamson! Length and on off, Kane blocks.
Kane Williamson walks out to bat.

OUT! TAKEN! What a catch that is! What a start that is for India after the break! Not sure what they had for lunch but whatever it was, has worked. Credit though to Gill. The wicket has been taken by Yadav but it is Gill who needs to be credited. First ball after a break, you probably would be on your heels as a fielder but that is not the case here, excellent effort and an excellent take. Yadav, from around the wicket, bangs it short and on the body. William Somerville takes on the challenge of pulling it, he hits it uppishly towards fine leg. Gill rushes in, dives forward and takes it inches above the ground. The Indians are delighted. William Somerville walks back after playing a gritty knock. The nightwatchman surely did his job. However, this will lift the Indian spirits.
Commentary.Howout: c Shubman Gill b Umesh Yadav

Commentary.Commentary: The second session is set to get underway! The Indian players stride out to the middle. Tom Latham and William Somerville are at the crease. Umesh Yadav to start after Lunch.
... DAY 5, SESSION 2 ...

Now just the 59 overs left in the day's play! India need 9 wickets and New Zealand just over 200 runs. The latter result looks highly unlikely as the Kiwis themselves seem to be playing for a draw. Will we see a change in approach though by them or will India weave their magic after Lunch? We will find out at 12:10 pm Local (6:40 am GMT)!

India on the other hand, have to continue to be patient. They would know, a wicket here could change things as it is not easy to begin on this wicket. For now, though, the wicket seems to have eased out quite a lot. There is a delivery or two which has spun big but apart from that, it still looks a good one to bat on. The hosts though would hope things change after the break.

New Zealand's first task when they began today morning would be to get through the first session with minimal damage and they have passed that with flying colors! Really don't think they themselves would have expected to go unscathed into the Lunch break. Top, top stuff from Latham and William. They have looked solid, assured and have shown great character so far. Yes, the wicket probably does not have a lot of demons in it but the two have played brilliantly. They still can't rest on their laurels though as there is still a long way to go.
Tossed up, outside off. Left alone and that is Lunch on Day 5!
This comes in with the angle and is blocked out.

Sharp turn! Tossed up, outside off. It lands in the rough and turns away sharply. Latham gets forward to defend but is beaten. The keeper and the man at first slip fail to stop it. Two byes are taken.
Shorter ball, outside off. Latham works it to mid on.
Full and on the pads. Worked past square leg for one.
Tossed up, on the pads. William Somerville blocks it out.
Shorter again, outside off. William Somerville pushes it past covers for one.
Short of a length, outside off. Left alone.
A run out decision has been sent upstairs! Looked like Tom Latham was home but the on-field umpires will confirm it. The replays suggest the same and Latham survives.

NOT OUT! Short of a length, on middle and leg. William Somerville works it towards square leg. The throw comes in and hits the stumps at the striker's end and then deflects. The batters take an overthrow. The TV umpire is called in but Latham is well inside.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Latham works it past mid-wicket. Ravindra Jadeja chases it and dives to stop it. Three taken.
Full ball, on off. Pushed to mid off.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Another one staying low! Flatter ball, on a length, outside off. Somerville stays back to defend but the ball straightens, keeps low and goes past his blade.
Fuller ball, on the pads. Blocked out.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Short and outside off. William Somerville rocks back and pushes it to the cover fence.
This turns back in but William Somerville keeps it out well.
Loopy ball, outside off. William Somerville plays for the turn but the ball goes straight and goes past his attempted defence.
Flatter ball, on the pads. Latham works it past square leg for one.
Short ball, around leg. William Somerville ducks under it.
Length ball, on the pads. Latham works it to fine leg for a single now.
On a length, angling across off. Latham pushes it to the right of mid off.
Full ball, on off. Pushed to mid off by Latham.
Length ball, on off. Latham blocks it from the crease.
Length ball, outside off. Pushed to covers.

Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, angling across off. William Somerville pushes it to the off side.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on off. Pushed to the off side. Ashwin goes after the ball and Latham wants a single but William Somerville sends him back.
Shorter, on leg. Latham works it past mid-wicket for one.

Ravichandran Ashwin (9-2-12-1) is back on.
That stayed low! Flatter ball, on a length, around off. William Somerville stays back to defend but the ball stays low and hits the toe end of his bat.
Tossed up, on a length, around off. William Somerville defends it off the front foot.
On a length, around middle. William Somerville prods to block this one out.

Flatter ball, on a length, around off. William Somerville defends it off the front foot.

Another ball, fuller in length, outside off. Latham gets to the pitch of the ball and sweeps it towards deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Tom Latham blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter ball, outside off. Latham hangs back and turns it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on a length, around middle and leg. William Somerville presses forward and pushes it to mid on.
Fuller in length, around leg. Somerville turns it behind square on the leg side.
Loopy ball, around middle. Somerville defends it out.
Flatter ball, around off. William Somerville blocks it solidly off the front foot.
Flatter ball, coming in with the angle from middle. William Somerville turns it to short leg with soft hands.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Latham defends it to the off side and takes off for a single.
Tossed up, on a length, around off. William Somerville gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks.
Flatter ball, around off. William Somerville rocks back and punches it to cover.
Tossed up, on a length, around middle. William Somerville turns it to the leg side.
On a length, around off. William Somerville defends it out.
Flatter ball, turning away a bit and staying low, around middle. William Somerville blocks it out.
Just a tad short, outside off. Latham works it behind square on the off side and rotates the strike.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off. William Somerville is solid in his defence yet again.
Loopy ball, fuller in length, around middle. Latham moves across a bit and flicks it to deep square leg for a run.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Tom Latham defends it out.
Darted on the pads. Latham tucks it to square leg.
Another ball, flatter and quicker, around off. Latham presses forward to defend this one.
Flatter ball, on off. Latham blocks it off the front foot.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Shorter ball, lands around off and turns away sharply. William Somerville goes back to block but gets beaten.
Latham sweeps this behind square on the leg side for one.

Is that a drop? Loopy ball, outside off. Latham looks to block but misses. There is a sound as the ball goes past the bat but Srikar Bharat does not gather it. There doesn't seem to be any bat on it. Maybe, the sound of bat hitting the ground or the pad.
Fuller and on off. Blocked out.

Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.

Back of a length, around middle and leg. William Somerville tucks it to the leg side and takes a single to keep the strike for the next over.
Short of a length, angling in from middle. Latham sits back and turns it towards fine leg for a run.

They would want these two to bat as long as possible here. For India, patience is the name of the game as one wicket might be enough to turn the game on its head.

Ajinkya Rahane opts for a review but the Ball Tracker suggests that the impact was way outside off so the on-field decision stays and Tom Latham survives!
Review time! India review this for LBW but the impact might be outside off. No bat on that. But the impact is at least two stumps outside off.

We are set to get the final day underway! Ajinkya Rahane has his team in a huddle before leading India out on the field. Seems like Srikar Bharat is still the man with gloves. Tom Latham and William Somerville walk out to bat. Ravichandran Ashwin is set to start with the ball.

PITCH REPORT - Simon Doull says that the pitch hasn't deteriorated as much as he expected at the start of the Test. Adds that New Zealand need to bat really well against spin and especially against Axar Patel. Deep Dasgupta says that the batters should look to use the feet against the spin. He adds that it still looks okay to bat on but it is going to be hard work for the visitors.

Have to say, an India win looks the most likely. We saw the pitch starting to play tricks towards the end of Day 4 and it is not going to get any easier. One thing is for sure, we are going to see a lot of spin from the Indians today. The Kiwis will need a spectacular effort from one of their stars if they are going to have any chance. Do they have a hero in their side?

Hello and welcome to the coverage of the last day of what has been an excellent first Test between India and New Zealand. The game is perfectly set up for a fascinating finish. All three results are highly likely. India need 9 wickets, the Kiwis require another 280 runs and both have 90 overs to complete their respective tasks. Will we see a side take a lead or is it going to remain 0-0 heading into the next game? Stay tuned...
... DAY 5, SESSION 1 ...

A lot will now depend on the New Zealand middle order, the likes of Latham, Williamson and Taylor will hold the key! They need to step up because that is probably the only chance the Kiwis have to save or win this game. India on the other hand, need to be patient, the wicket is worsening as the game progresses and if they bowl the right lines and lengths, it is not going to be easy for the visitors. What will the final result be then? We will find out on Day 5. The action begins at 9:30 am local (4 am GMT) so set your alarms accordingly. Till then, take care and goodbye!

Shreyas Iyer is down for a chat. He says that he has been in such situations before during his Ranji Trophy days so he was looking to spend time at the crease. Adds that he knew that he would be the first Indian to score a hundred and a fifty on his debut but winning is what matters. States that it was difficult to curb his attacking instincts but the instructions from Rahul Dravid were to bat as long as possible. Informs that there wasn't much happening on the wicket so they wanted to get to a competitive total before declaring the innings.

New Zealand will be mighty disappointed that they could not press home the advantage given by their pacers this morning. Iyer, Saha, Patel and Ashwin bailed India out of trouble. India declared with not many overs left in the day, they started with their spinners and that worked as they have broken the opening partnership which really troubled them in the first innings.

India's day without any doubt! We surely did not think we would be writing that after the first session but now, the visitors have their backs against the wall. They would have loved to enter Day 5 unscathed and that could have well been the case had they taken the review in time. But that is not the case and the hosts need 9 wickets to win the game whereas the visitors have to score 280 to take a 1-0 lead. A draw is also quite possible but a result seems on the cards.

OUT! LBW! Will Young runs out of time to review it! Tossed up, this lands outside off. Stays low and comes back in. Young looks to block but gets hit on the pads. The finger is raised. Young has a chat with Latham and it is a long chat. The timer runs out and then Young shows the sign for a review. The Indian fielders immediately point that out and the umpire too, is aware of it and denies the review. OH MY, MY! The ball was spinning down the leg stumps! If only Young had been a bit quicker to review. Early wicket for India, they would love another one too.

So, Saha is seen going back into the dressing room! He was struggling with a neck issue, even while batting he never looked 100 percent. Bharat comes in place of him. He was very impressive in the first innings too.
